The corneal dendritic branching ulcer with terminal bulbs that stained with rose bengal and multinucleated giant cells suggest herpes simplex virus (HSV)-1, which is a common cause of viral conjunctivitis and keratitis. Acanthamoeba and Pseudomonas are common causes of contact lens-associated keratitis, but they do not present with corneal dendritic branching ulcers. Candida albicans is a common cause of fungal conjunctivitis, but it does not typically cause corneal dendritic branching ulcers.
